column1: #This file contains all putative binding regions identified by the automated putative binding site algorithm.
#The ‘start’ and ‘end’ columns are with respect to the predicted TSS contained in supplementary file 1. Negative base pairs are upstream of the TSS.
#Activators that overlap with activator (in the same growth condition), or repressorressors that overlap with repressorressors are treated as one larger site.
#As different growth conditions can alter the concentration and DNA binding activity of Tfs, binding sites might not appear in all growth conditions
#Final repressororted binding sites in the paper can be either found in this table or have additional evidence for their presence.

#However, many of the binding sites here will be removed manually before repressororting, the reasons for which can be found in the methods sections of the paper. Additionally, some sites will have been split into two sites manually.

column6: Is the putative binding site predicted to contain part of an RNAP site?
